[362-484. The boxing bout. Dares, a great Trojan boxer, alone offers, and after a pause claims the prize. Acestes urges the aged boxer Entellus to compete, who reluctantly agrees, and challenges Dares. Dares eluding a blow, Entellus falls heavily, and exasperated thereby beats Dares all over the field. Aeneas stops the fight. En- tellus slays with a blow the prize ox to Eryx his hero-patron.]
